{"tid":1263328,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"今日收到HR封email...","createTime":"2019-06-28T06:25:01.000Z","updateTime":"2019-06-28T06:49:04.000Z","uid":53377,"like":4,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":5,"replies":[{"pid":"3664f46646ec5da2ed12abf5153160711dacb3e7","tid":1263328,"uid":53377,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-06-28T06:25:01.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/QLyToWJ.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FQLyToWJ.png&h=4a1606d9&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\nDear all<br />\nIn view of the recent protests in Hong Kong, this email serves to provide you with some information about the Group Life and Medical insurance coverages for the Hong Kong office:<br />\nBy and large, there is no specific exclusion on &ldquo;protests&rdquo; under the group life and medical policies, however, please be mindful of the below exclusions:<br />\nGroup Medical (BUPA):<br />\n- <strong><span style=\"color: red;\">Treatment relating to any illness or bodily injury resulting from participation in criminal activities.</span></strong><br />\nGroup Life (Generali):<br />\n- AD&amp;D and TPD benefit: <span style=\"color: red;\"><strong>Active, passive participation in war, declared or undeclared, civil war, revolution, riot, civil commotion, strike, insurrection or criminal activities.</strong></span><br />\nShould you have any questions, please feel free to contact us.<br />\nKind regards<br />\nHuman Resources<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 公司好嘢"},{"pid":"b73071849441ac6e07fab8cfe5cebff0ee3ce3ad","tid":1263328,"uid":54303,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-06-28T06:26:06.000Z","msg":"姐係話冇比人拉就有得claim?<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"d8aaa2fdd5e0b7cf205bb6e54bdeb42053e7487d","tid":1263328,"uid":53377,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":